## Importing a WSDL file
> Important

The system only allows to import files using the Document / Literal (wrapped) style. Thus, it is necessary to convert different styles, e.g. RPC / encoded, to the supported one.

It is only possible to import WSDL files with simple objects, such as strings and integers in the signature and in the return value.

- Open the Web Service resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources).

-  If no WSDL file has been imported yet, click **UPLOAD FILE **and select the required WSDL file from your filesystem. The **Web Service configuration **panel is displayed, showing the properties of the imported file.
